ersity of Tennessee  Jeff is married to Lisa Smith  and they have two boys  Jeffrey and Phillip  ages 17 and 16 respectively  Jeff s career in the Air Force spanned three different occupational specialties and two continents  He started as a second lieutenant ICBM missile launcher officer  spent approximately ten years working in various financial managements jobs both in the U S  and Germany  and for the last ten years he was either in school or teaching  first at the Air Force s graduate school  and finally at the United States Air Force Academy  Jennifer E  Gerow earned a Ph D  in Management  concentration  Information Systems  from Clemson University  She also has an MBA and a Bachelor of Science in Biological Sciences with a minor in Secondary Education  She has 9 years of industry experience in e commerce  Her research interests are power and politics in the workplace  IT business strategic alignment  and motivation to use information systems  Jennifer and Charles  her husband  are both excited about joining the VMI family  Valentina Dimitrova Grajzl received her Ph D  in Economics from the University of Maryland  College Park  in 2006  She also holds a Master s degree from UMD and a Bachelor s Degree from Wittenberg University  She was previously an assistant professor at the Department of Public Policy at the Central European University and a visiting assistant professor at Washington and Lee University s Economics Department  Her teaching and research focuses on economics of institutions  post socialist economies and politics  economic history  and law and economics    Spring 2011 Newsletter  Field Test  Faculty Research  TAPS  New Faculty  Lopez Chair  Alumni in the News  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  BGS   ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI 